East 6th Street, north side, east from, but not including Lewis Street, to the East River. Shown in the foreground, is No. 815 a 1-story frame building.

September 11, 1935.

P. L. Sperr.

East 6th Street, east from Lewis Street to the East River. Across the latter appears the Williamsburg (Brooklyn) shore.

November 9, 1936.

W.P.A.Photo.
Federal Art Project.

203 and 217 Lewis Street, west side, north from and including East 6th, to but not including East 7th Streets. Also shown is a clearance at the N.W. corner of East 6th Street and a 7-story structure (No. 203) in a state of disuse. This is part of the area which was developed for the East River Drive by the Works Progress Administration.
February 24, 1937.

P. L. Sperr.
